cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.IR 

This paper is about a deep neural network method for sentence classification, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP). The method uses both long-range dependencies within the sentence and potentially large contexts formed from adjacent sentences. Therefore, it is likely to be relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
